{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Timothy 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:1",
      "text": "But understand this, that in the last days there will come times of stress.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:2",
      "text": "For men will be lovers of self, lovers of money, proud, arrogant, abusive, disobedient to their parents, ungrateful, unholy,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:3",
      "text": "inhuman, implacable, slanderers, profligates, fierce, haters of good,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:4",
      "text": "treacherous, reckless, swollen with conceit, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:5",
      "text": "holding the form of religion but denying the power of it. Avoid such people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:6",
      "text": "For among them are those who make their way into households and capture weak women, burdened with sins and swayed by various impulses,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:7",
      "text": "who will listen to anybody and can never arrive at a knowledge of the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:8",
      "text": "As Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these men also oppose the truth, men of corrupt mind and counterfeit faith;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:9",
      "text": "but they will not get very far, for their folly will be plain to all, as was that of those two men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:10",
      "text": "Now you have observed my teaching, my conduct, my aim in life, my faith, my patience, my love, my steadfastness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:11",
      "text": "my persecutions, my sufferings, what befell me at Antioch, at Iconium, and at Lystra, what persecutions I endured; yet from them all the Lord rescued me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:12",
      "text": "Indeed all who desire to live a godly life in Christ Jesus will be persecuted,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:13",
      "text": "while evil men and impostors will go on from bad to worse, deceivers and deceived.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:14",
      "text": "But as for you, continue in what you have learned and have firmly believed, knowing from whom you learned it",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:15",
      "text": "and how from childhood you have been acquainted with the sacred writings which are able to instruct you for salvation through faith in Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:16",
      "text": "All scripture is inspired by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, and for training in righteousness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:second-timothy.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 3:17",
      "text": "that the man of God may be complete, equipped for every good work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
